did.abstract: The Fred Crawford Papers consists of the research material gathered by Central Michigan University Professor Fred Crawford from 1991 to 1998 for a biography on Lowell Thomas.

scopecontent.head: Collection Overview
scopecontent.p: The Fred Crawford Papers consists of the research material gathered by Central Michigan University Professor Fred Crawford from 1991 to 1998 for a biography on Lowell Thomas. Most of the material within the collection appears to have been maintained in an orderly fashion by Fred Crawford. The lone exception to this is Series 2 which may have been the material Crawford was currently working on as well as assorted on-hand and reference material. While the order within most of the file series was not maintained during the transport to Marist College, the original order was recreated during processing based on the detail of Crawford’s original folder descriptions. These descriptions were maintained when possible with alterations made only for consistency and completion. Misfiles that appeared to be organic were maintained to preserve as much of Crawford’s original and unique order as possible.

acqinfo.head: Acquisitions Information
acqinfo.p: The Fred Crawford Papers were gathered from 1991 to 1998 by Fred Crawford while he was researching the life of Lowell Thomas for a planned biography. After his death, his wife MaryAnn Crawford (also a CMU professor of English) attempted to sell the collection to another researcher that would take up the challenge of a Thomas biography. She may or may not have contributed to the comprehensive labeling and organization of the collection. After she was unable to find a buyer, she donated the collection to Marist College in 2012.

bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: Fred Crawford was Professor of English at Central Michigan University who researched Lowell Thomas for a biography from 1991 – 1998.

arrangement.p: Collection is arranged into thirteen series: 1) Original Material from Lowell Thomas Papers, has three subseries, 2) Fred Crawford mixed research and reference file, 3) IOC File: Individual research correspondence, 4) AC: Administrative Correspondence, 5) External research file, 6) Lowell Thomas papers research file, 7) AMT File, 8) Marianna Munn Thomas file, 9) Boxed chronological materials=, has four subseries, 10) Photographs, 11) Objects, 12)Audio Recordsings, has eight subseries, and 13, Video Tapes
Materials are arranged by subject or chronologically

2. Fred Crawford Mixed Research and Reference File

scopecontent.p: Series 2 includes Crawford’s mixed research material such as reference material, research notes, and other material that seems to been on–hand or not yet permanently filed.

Files labeled “Lowell Thomas research – 'Other Archives'” seems to consist of research material Crawford used for his completed writings like chapter drafts and his article co – written with Joe Berton. These files were originally one large file, and the order was maintained as found.
Material labeled “Lowell Thomas research in progress” seems to be the items that were last pursued by Crawford or were otherwise on – hand.

The Hoover Library Oral Histories are photocopies of oral history interviews of Herbert Hoover gathered by the presidential library. The original order of these files was maintained. One interview was given by Lowell Thomas.
The FBI dossiers feature correspondence between Thomas and J. Edgar Hoover as well as the investigation of Thomas prior to his 1974 Presidential Medal of Freedom award

Video Images presents a Video Yesteryear recording: 100. BORNEO. (1937) Adventure documentary with MARTIN and OSA JOHNSON. Narrated by LOWELL THOMAS. Featuring " Wildmen of Borneo " , tree - climbing fish, and flying snakes! Recommended! 76 minutes

Video Images presents a Video Yesteryear recording: 241. SEE IT NOW (June 9, 1957). CBS - TV. " Automation. " EDWARD R. MURROW narrating. How Automation is changing American industry, unemployment, and the way we live. 82 minutes. [unopened]

Video Images presents a Video Yesteryear recording: 243. IT'S NEWS TO ME (c. July 1954). CBS - TV net. A young WALTER CRONKITE moderating a panel/game show based on (then) current news events. 30 minutes. [unopened]

Video Images presents a Video Yesteryear recording: 366. THE STORY OF TELEVISION (June 20, 1956) PARTIAL COLOR. Documentary history of TV, including rare scenes of station W2XBS and Dr. VLADIMIR ZWORTKIN! 27 minutes.

Video Images presents a Video Yesteryear recording: 448. THINGS TO COME. (1936) With RAYMOUND MASSEY, RALPH RICHARDSON, SIR CEDRIC HARDWICK. Written by H.G. WELLS. Spectacular classic of the future. 92 minutes.

Video Images presents a Video Yesteryear recording: 485. BEHIND YOUR RADIO DIAL and WESTINGHOUSE PRESENTS (1948). NBC industrial film about " today's " radio, and a complete broadcast on film with JOHN CHARLES THOMAS. 45 minutes total. [unopened]

Video Images presents a Video Yesteryear recording: 1157. CONQUEST OF EVEREST (1953) COLOR. The story of Edmund Hillary's conquest of Mount Everest. Named one of the 10 best films of the year! 78 minutes. [unopened]

Video Images presents a Video Yesteryear recording: 1212. THE JACK BENNY PROGRAM (October 18, 1959) CBS - TV. With JACK BENNY, DON WILSON, THE SPORTSMEN, former President HARRY TRUMAN. 25 minutes. [unopened]

Video Images presents a Video Yesteryear recording: 2222. BABOONA (1935 - USA) With MARTIN and OSA JOHNSON, A fine wildlife nature film with the couple who invented the idea of bringing wild animals to the movie screen. Well done! 73 minutes. [unopened]

Video Images presents a Video Yesteryear recording: 2261. THE SPIRIT OF " 43 " AND MORE! (1941 - 1950's - USA) PARTIAL COLOR. Four Short films. " The Spirit of " 43, " " The House I Live In, " " Soldiers in Greasepaint, " and " Women in Defense. " 56 minutes total. [unopened]

Video Images presents a Video Yesteryear recording: 2280. WITH BYRD AT THE SOUTH POLE(1930 - USA) With ADMIRAL RICHARD BYRD. The beautifully photographed story of the first flight over the South Pole by Byrd and his men. Well done! 83 minutes. [unopened]

Video Images presents a Video Yesteryear recording: 2289. SIMBA (1928 - USA) With OSA and MARTIN JOHNSON. A superb example of the work of the famous jungle cinematographers. " Silent " film with music score. 86 minutes.
Video Images presents a Video Yesteryear recording: 2524. THE JEEP GOES TO WAR! (1942 - c.1944 - USA) Five government films showing Jeeps, half - tracks and tanks in action. 54 minutes total.

Video Images presents a Video Yesteryear recording: 2920. A GREAT RAILROAD AT WORK (1942 - USA) Narrated by LOWELL THOMAS. A portrait of the New York, New Haven and Hartford Railroad, how it is operated and how it is maintained. 47 minutes.

Video Images presents a Video Yesteryear recording: 2993. HEAVY METAL: STUDEBAKER, NASH, HUDSON and KAISER (1952 - 1955 - USA) PARTIAL COLOR. " Nash For 1953/1955, " Hudson commercial, " Studebaker Story " and " Word Of Honor. " 65 minutes total.
